AviDemo (console command)
=========================

Description
-----------

This command will play a .[DEMO](DEMO\_(file\_format)) and output the frames as a .[TGA](TGA\_(file\_format)) images.

Usage
-----

At the console type...

`aviDemoÂ [Filename]`

Parameters
----------

-   [Filename] - Name of .DEMO file (without the extension).

Notes
-----

This command will generate a lot of .[TGA](TGA\_(file\_format)) files, be sure to free up disk space before running it. Related CVars:

-   [com\_aviDemoHeight](Com\_aviDemoHeight\_(cvar)) - You can select the height of each frame.
-   [com\_aviDemoSamples](Com\_aviDemoSamples\_(cvar)) - You can select the [antialiasing](Antialiasing) factor of each frame.
-   [com\_aviDemoTics](Com\_aviDemoTics\_(cvar)) - You can select how many frames per second should be generated.
-   [com\_aviDemoWidth](Com\_aviDemoWidth\_(cvar)) - You can select the width of each frame.

Tutorial on creating Avi demos: [Recording Avi Demos](http://web.archive.org/web/20120126050326/http://doom.freakygaming.com/tutorials/record_avi_videos_in_doom_3.html)


